This paper is primarily focused on intrusion detection in real-time embedded systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques (global k-means clustering) to learn legitimate execution contexts, which could potentially fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions minor processor modifications to aid in the intrusion detection process, which could fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
